==English==

===Etymology===
From Ancient Greek ''[[an]]'' ([[without]]), ''[[archos]]'' ([[leader]] - [[governance]] - [[rulership]])

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-}}

# Any theory or doctrine that proposes the [[absence]] of involuntary [[government]] in all forms.
# ''Specifically'', a political philosophical belief that all forms of involuntary rule or government is [[undesirable]] or [[unnecessary]] and that society could function without a ruler or government in a [[socialist]] order, perhaps with a non hierarchy leader (possible only present for reasons of keeping peace and defense).
*[[anarchy]]

